/wp/v2/posts?per_page=100&#038;page=1&#038;status=publish%2Cdraft%2Cfuture%2Cpending%2Cprivate&#038;_fields=id%2Cslug%2Ctitle%2Cstatus%2Ccontent%2Cexcerpt%2Cfeatured_media%2Cdate%2Clink&#038;add-to-cart=24519\" aria-describedby=\"woocommerce_loop_add_to_cart_link_describedby_24519\" data-quantity=\"1\" class=\"button product_type_simple add_to_cart_button ajax_add_to_cart add-to-cart-loop\" data-product_id=\"24519\" data-product_sku=\"\" aria-label=\"Add to cart: &ldquo;Lepidolite Pyramid&rdquo;\" rel=\"nofollow\" data-success_message=\"&ldquo;Lepidolite Pyramid&rdquo; has been added to your cart\" role=\"button\"><span class=\"wd-action-icon\"><span class=\"wd-check-icon\"></span></span><span class=\"wd-action-text\">Add to cart</span></a>\t<span id=\"woocommerce_loop_add_to_cart_link_describedby_24519\" class=\"screen-reader-text\">\n\t\t\t</span>\n\t</div>\n\n\t\n\t\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t</div>\n</div>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">FAQ About Crystals for Peace</h2>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Can crystals bring me peace or calm?</h3>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Not on their own. Crystals can&#8217;t grant peace. Many people use them as tangible cues to pause and soften; lasting calm comes from habits, rest, and sometimes support. For persistent unease or anxiety, a healthcare professional is the right call.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Are crystals scientifically proven to bring peace?</h3>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">No. There is no clinical evidence that crystals themselves create peace. Any felt benefit usually comes from the ritual of pausing, not a proven effect of the stone.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Which crystal is best for peace and calm?</h3>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Chrysocolla and angelite are the most commonly chosen — chrysocolla for inner calm, angelite for a gentle, soft landing.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">What is the best crystal for a busy, racing mind?</h3>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Amethyst and prehnite — amethyst to let the chatter settle, prehnite to help the noise quiet.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Which crystal helps me clear mental clutter?</h3>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Selenite is often used to clear the mind and make space for calm.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">How should I cleanse peace crystals?</h3>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Smoke (sage, palo santo), sound (singing bowl), or moonlight work for most stones. Note that selenite and angelite are water-sensitive — keep them dry and avoid water cleansing.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">What is the best crystal bracelet for peace?</h3>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">An amethyst bracelet is the most common first choice — durable, widely available, and easy to wear daily as a quiet reminder to soften.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Explore More Crystal Guides</h2>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><li><a href=\"/crystals-for-anxiety/\">Crystals for Anxiety</a></li><li><a href=\"/crystals-for-stress/\">Crystals for Stress</a></li><li><a href=\"/crystals-for-sleep/\">Crystals for Sleep</a></li><li><a href=\"/crystals-for-meditation/\">Crystals for Meditation</a></li><li><a href=\"/crystals-for-balance/\">Crystals for Balance</a></li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Peace is a stance more than a setting — and a real stone can be a steady cue to soften inside the noise. Start with one and let small pauses add up. For more, explore <a href=\"/calm-mindfulness/\">Calm &amp; Mindfulness</a>.</p>\n",
